track.name: Way Down in the Hole
comments: And I do mean the ones of you who think it's of significance where you find music.
I miss The Wire so much.
No, not in a hole, but wondering why artists need to take advantage of other artists without paying them.
Yes, because the most important part is how you stumble across music, not that you actually enjoy it.
Is that why I have friends who have actually heard of Tom Waits now?  The goddamn Wire?  That's slightly disappointing.  I thought my school chums were getting their avant-garde on.
It grew a lot on me after watching The Wire.

We got to go in with our hydraulic system and blast him out!
People, can I get an amen?
Breath-taking. Tom's voice is so sexy.
the wire's second season blowing my mind right now.
I'll have to agree! "Hamburg 1987 bootleg version, holy shit." [2]
What the fuck did I do?
